original_title: Five MoUs signed between India and Sri Lanka
original_body_lines: Five Memorandums of Understanding (MoUs) including a MoU on Renewable Energy, and Solar Power Project were signed between India and Sri Lanka today.
The MoUs were exchanged in the presence of Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Sri Lanka President Ranil Wickremesinghe.

The MoUs that were signed are a Memorandum of Cooperation for Economic Development of Projects in the Trincomalee District, Renewable Energy, an Energy permit for the solar power project and Network to network agreement between IPL and Lanka Pay for the UPI application acceptance, and an MoU on Animal husbandry.
